# {{DISPLAY_NAME}}

This is a canonical provider adapter scaffold.

Use it to:

- materialize a provider-truth OpenAPI slice
- expose the provider-native method surface
- declare the Nex projection contract for ingest, backfill, monitor, and routing
- prove auth, setup, health, and representative provider behavior

Keep the boundary explicit:

- one package: provider-native methods plus the Nex projection contract
- optional convenience wrappers may exist, but they do not replace the full
  provider surface

When you flesh this scaffold out, do not forget the default hardening rules:

- setup/bootstrap and direct reads should be resilient to provider rate limits
- heavy binary/provider reads should return attachment-backed metadata instead
  of inline base64 payloads
